        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 7:07PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 705 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Citrus City, or near La Joya, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Narciso G. Cavazos Elementary School, Edinburg North High School, Red
Gate, Abram-Perezville, Cesar Chavez Middle School, Doffing, John F
Kennedy Elementary School, Lorenzo De Zavala Middle School, Palmview
High School, and Citrus City.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 83 between mile markers 844 and 850.
Interstate Highway 69 C between mile markers 9 and 12.
US Highway 281 between mile markers 762 and 764.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
